contributor: des barres, joseph f. w. (joseph frederick wallet)
description: L.C. copy no. 21 of the Atlantic Neptune, with 52 items. Charts dated 1775 to 1778. This collection seems to have been sold separately, without the general t.p., but with the sectional title. The Nova Scotia title, a leaf of "General remarks," and a leaf of "References" are repeated in each volume. Vol. 1 has an engr. table of contents listing 14 numbered items; v. 2, a contemporary manuscript list with entries numbered 2 to 36. Two charts called for are wanting. Cf. H. N. Stevens. Catalogue of the Henry Newton Stevens collection of the Atlantic Neptune. Available also through the Library of Congress Web site as a raster image.

contributors: Des Barres, Joseph F. W. (Joseph Frederick Wallet), 1729-1824
